{
  "stem": "1062.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Somebody would give the flour in another site.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He would-- he was called a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the middle, there was Reb Shmiel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a small guy, with a long white beard.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he would knead the dough.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it had to be done very fast because if you let the dough stay there, so the dough would rise, and it wouldn't be kosher.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he did it very fast.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, Passover time, we used to find a lot of hair from Shmiel's beard inside the-- inside the-- inside with the matzahs, you know, because he was kneading it so fast, he's-- even his-- you know, piece of the beard would fall in.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But that was OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was kosher.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "After they took out the dough from Shmiel's, you know, when he was finished kneading it, there was a long table.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And somebody stood there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was known as a [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In other words, he would rip off a piece of the dough and gave it to the woman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He was known as the [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Woman would stay in line in either side of the table.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Maybe there were about 25, 30 woman.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they would roll out the matzah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "After the matzah was rolled out, somebody would take it over to another table, where it would go through a wheel-- a wheel full of spokes, so when the matzah heats up, it shouldn't blow up.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So the matzah has-- I think even-- even today's matzah has little spokes in it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That's the reasoning.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Even today's matzah has it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would-- they would roll over with a-- a little wheel with spokes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was known as a reddler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then somebody would take the matzah and put it on a-- what do you call that rolling stone-- the rolling stick?",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
